my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:11:1. **Memory of place.** A continuous rolling buffer of contact + room input. When something is acoustically interesting (a transient cluster, a novel spectral signature, a sustained drone the room produces on its own), the buffer is captured to disk, tagged with the arc phase / mood / time / who-is-in-room, and made available to future scenes. Days later, those moments return — never literally, always granularly transformed — as quiet textures. The room composes itself through CypherClaw.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:20:2. **Memory-tagged, mood-aware selection.** Samples carry rich metadata. The sample-selector matches samples to current artist mode, arc phase, harmonic context, and mood — never random. A sample picked for *Solitary* mode will never appear in *Working ambience* mode unless the metadata aligns.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:29:**In scope:** a granular SuperCollider voice (`sw_sampler`) with a dedicated effects bus; a sample library on disk with tag-based selection; a continuous live-capture daemon for contact/room mics; a self-quotation loop; integration with the existing artist-mode selector and cast planner so the sampler joins the signature quintet; metrics and anti-pattern detection for sampler over- or under-use.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:34:- ML-based sound classification or auto-tagging from raw audio. Tags come from acoustic-feature heuristics (transient density, spectral centroid, RMS, pitch confidence) — interpretable and debuggable.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:42:**Phase 1 — Foundations (CCS-001..CCS-008).** Sample data model, on-disk library layout, tag taxonomy, mood/mode-aware selector, character-registry entry for `voice_sampler`, signature-voice quintet update. Pure Python + tests. At end of phase, the selector picks plausible samples for any (mode, arc, mood) tuple from a library of stub/placeholder files; no audio plays yet.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:46:**Phase 3 — Live capture daemon (CCS-015..CCS-021).** `sample_capture_daemon.py` maintains rolling 60-second buffers of contact mic + room mic via JACK input; an interesting-moment detector flags acoustically novel windows; flagged windows get saved to `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` with auto-generated tags (arc phase, mood, time, who-is-in-room, acoustic features); systemd unit keeps the daemon running. End of phase: leaving the daemon running for an hour produces ~10–30 tagged WAV files representing the room's acoustic life.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:48:**Phase 4 — Composer integration (CCS-022..CCS-028).** Mode-driven sampler density (solitary heavy, working light, etc.); `select_sample()` wired into cast/instrument-patch path so the composer treats the sampler as a first-class voice; self-quotation loop captures composer output when arc-payoff is high; keyboard/Theramini capture during human play; per-mode effects-bus presets; operator diagnostics surface currently-active samples. End of phase: pieces start to noticeably *cite themselves* across sessions, and the room's acoustic history becomes audible material.
