 - Hardened sampler buffer cap enforcement: `BufferLoader` now rejects non-positive capacities, routes overflow eviction through `on_sampler_free()` before issuing new `/b_alloc` + `/b_allocRead` traffic, and has a regression test that fills the default 64-buffer pool and verifies the full load/evict cycle.
 - Added listener-review workflow: `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` documents weekly review cadence, step-by-step rule ablation via the `senseweave-render-debugger` CLI (CCH-010), and how to attach review notes; `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` provides a structured template with piece, date, felt_wrong, suspected_rule, ablation_result, and action fields; `render.listener_review` validates artifact integrity and anchors the documented CLI name to the live debugger parser.
